title: I’m writing Good Omens Fic
body:
“The Sociological Behavior of Courting Demons and Angels” so far:

The concept is that Newt and Anathema’s daughter is psychic and now in college, she procrastinated on a paper and as such has to write the entire thing in one night.

She uses her true and accurate Second Sight to observe and document the Courting Rituals of Angels and Demons

Crowley and Aziraphale’s unfortunate dance of trying to finally get to the other one ensues.

title: Unforgivable
body:
read it on the AO3 at https://ift.tt/2FuCyX5

by aalisse

Crowley was feeding ducks and waiting for Aziraphale. He didn’t expect to have a chat with God, but then again, who would?
_____
“The Almighty turns to him. Aziraphale’s eyes grow two sizes. He tries to say something, but God claps him on the shoulder, and he closes his open mouth.

“I find the whole ordeal with the sword quite amusing,” She tells him. “I thought you should know.”

Aziraphale makes a noise that’s very close to a squeak. Crowley can’t blame him.”

summary: remember how people in 2006 used to make AMVs with anime and video games but instead of using music they would take the audio...
body:
remember how people in 2006 used to make AMVs with anime and video games but instead of using music they would take the audio from movie trailers and layer it over clips from the show/game

Now that we finally have a Good Omens mini series, someone needs to do that, except they need to use clips from the show to recreate the National Treasure trailer

You know, in order to bring Cage Omens to its natural peak

summary: Crowley: why oh why did I Fall, I only ever asked questions, ugh I’m so tragic  God: okay, pal, have you seen Heaven? have you...
body:
Crowley: why oh why did I Fall, I only ever asked questions, ugh I’m so tragic 

God: okay, pal, have you seen Heaven? have you seen Gabriel? do you think they have any creativity or appreciation for innovation? do you think they understand irony? do you think you could be as chaotic under Gabriel’s leadership? do you think you’d ever set your foot on Earth if you stayed there? friend, you’d be a clerk shuffling papers around, you’d be miserable.

title: Goodnight, goodnight
body:
Goodnight, goodnight, my dearest friend,

my comrade, the only one I want at my side.

I lock the doors and kill the lights

And know I will dream of you.

I’ll dream of golden eyes and savage rides and good laughs;

I’ll hear boot heals clicking out in the night, and hope it’s you.

It’s strange - this prickling under the skin, this space inside that’s you;

and I’d call it temptation, but it’s not like that all.

There is no lurking in the shadows, no deal, no trick;

for you’re pure flame, my darling, and there’s no shadow here.

You know how I am with these things, how hard to ‘pluck them out;

so I weave my heart in a string, and threaded it into an almost-rhyme;

it’s wonky and hasty and clumsy, but I’ll be better, and here I swear;

Once I’m in bed, too, I’ll close my eyes, and see you there.

Goodnight, goodnight, Raphael.

 

Aziraphale

so I weave my heart in a string, and threaded it into an almost-rhyme;

it’s wonky and hasty and clumsy, but I’ll be better, and here I swear;

Once I’m in bed, too, I’ll close my eyes, and see you there.

Goodnight, goodnight, Raphael.

 

Aziraphale
